title: signs and symptoms menu
description: A sudden sensation of feeling cold.
A sudden, audible expulsion of air from the lungs through a partially closed glottis, preceded by inhalation.
A subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation.
Body temperature elevated above the normal range.
Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.
A sensation of unease in the stomach together with an urge to vomit.
A red eruption of the skin.
Any kind of inflammatory process of the tonsils, pharynx, or/and larynx characterized by pain in swallowing.
Forceful ejection of the contents of the stomach through the mouth by means of a series of involuntary spasmic contractions.

title: pre-existing conditions and risk factors menu
exposure event menu
description: A gathering or event attended by a sufficient number of people to strain the planning and response resources of the host community, state/province, nation, or region where it is being held.
A gathering of individuals who meet at an arranged place and time in order to discuss or engage in some common interest. The most common conventions are based upon industry, profession, and fandom.
A gathering exhibiting the equipment, animals, sports and recreation associated with agriculture and animal husbandry.
A type of social behavior in which a collection of humans intentionally gathers together on a temporary basis to engage socially.
A human social event in which humans living in the same area or neighborhood gather to carry out activiites relevent to the people living in the area.
A human social gathering in which the intention is to have a good time. Often the intention is to celebrate something like a birthday, anniversary, or holiday, but there is not always a purpose.
An exposure event not specified in the picklist.
